1
00:00:07,933 --> 00:00:12,133
♪I've braved the storms, walked through the rain♪

2
00:00:12,167 --> 00:00:15,533
♪Seen the highs and lows along the way♪

3
00:00:15,733 --> 00:00:18,933
♪But you stay quiet, never change♪

4
00:00:19,133 --> 00:00:22,533
♪Like a child who dreams beneath the stars♪

5
00:00:22,600 --> 00:00:25,933
♪I've read the story in your eyes♪

6
00:00:26,167 --> 00:00:29,433
♪And finally, nothing's left to hide♪

7
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:33,033
♪You won't give in to a world so cold♪

8
00:00:33,167 --> 00:00:36,633
♪So you wander through it on your own♪

9
00:00:36,767 --> 00:00:40,233
♪Maybe fate has drawn us near♪

10
00:00:40,333 --> 00:00:43,233
♪Just to help you learn to believe♪

11
00:00:43,467 --> 00:00:46,400
♪Everything you've questioned deep inside♪

12
00:00:46,533 --> 00:00:50,633
♪I'll be the proof you need♪

13
00:00:50,767 --> 00:00:52,067
♪I've made my choice♪

14
00:00:52,167 --> 00:00:55,033
♪For you, I'll be brave and break the rules♪

15
00:00:55,400 --> 00:00:58,267
♪What's there to fear even if the world is right and I am wrong?♪

16
00:00:58,967 --> 00:01:01,833
♪One day, all of this will turn into memories♪

17
00:01:02,367 --> 00:01:05,267
♪Every storm we faced will turn into our life's scenery♪

18
00:01:06,033 --> 00:01:08,933
♪For you, I'll be brave and break the rules♪

19
00:01:09,233 --> 00:01:12,167
♪What's there to fear even if the world is right and I am wrong?♪

20
00:01:12,867 --> 00:01:15,733
♪Even if, in the end, the whole world turns against me♪

21
00:01:16,233 --> 00:01:19,167
♪I won't regret having loved you♪

22
00:01:19,267 --> 00:01:22,833
♪With all my heart♪

23
00:01:23,067 --> 00:01:26,667
♪I've held you close♪

24
00:01:26,767 --> 00:01:30,367
♪Walked by your side♪

25
00:01:30,533 --> 00:01:34,833
♪And loved the fire that burned inside you♪

26
00:01:34,833 --> 00:01:36,367
[The First Frost]

27
00:01:36,367 --> 00:01:37,867
[Adapted from the novel of the same name by Zhu Yi on www.jjwxc.net]

28
00:01:38,767 --> 00:01:44,633
[Beiyu]

29
00:01:50,033 --> 00:01:52,367
[Che Yanqin]

30
00:02:08,767 --> 00:02:10,167
The rain in Beiyu keeps falling.

31
00:02:11,333 --> 00:02:12,900
When will it stop?

32
00:02:16,600 --> 00:02:18,833
[Che Yanqin]

33
00:02:22,900 --> 00:02:23,967
Let's go watch a movie.

34
00:02:29,533 --> 00:02:32,667
[Ticket Office]

35
00:02:33,700 --> 00:02:34,733
Don't you

36
00:02:34,933 --> 00:02:35,800
study today?

37
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:38,600
I don't want you to look back and remember

38
00:02:38,600 --> 00:02:39,967
every time you came to Beiyu to see me

39
00:02:39,967 --> 00:02:41,367
all we did was read books.

40
00:02:41,767 --> 00:02:43,067
We should take a break when we need to.

41
00:02:49,833 --> 00:02:50,567
How about this one?

42
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:54,833
You like horror movies?

43
00:02:55,833 --> 00:02:56,700
I just picked it randomly.

44
00:02:58,600 --> 00:02:59,167
Is that okay?

45
00:02:59,300 --> 00:02:59,833
Sure!

46
00:03:00,933 --> 00:03:02,267
Hello, I want two tickets

47
00:03:02,267 --> 00:03:03,967
for Waking Up to Ghosts.

48
00:03:04,533 --> 00:03:05,367
Since then

49
00:03:07,367 --> 00:03:09,100
I've never gone back to school.

50
00:03:10,367 --> 00:03:11,833
I didn't even step outside.

51
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:13,833
No one understands me

52
00:03:15,367 --> 00:03:16,733
except for you.

53
00:03:17,300 --> 00:03:19,000
And no one ever talks to me.

54
00:03:28,133 --> 00:03:29,567
Why are you crying again?

55
00:03:30,833 --> 00:03:32,967
Don't you think that you can forget a lot of things

56
00:03:34,033 --> 00:03:35,767
when watching horror movies?

57
00:03:35,933 --> 00:03:37,400
Can't other movies make you do that?

58
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:39,700
It seems horror movies are better for that.

59
00:03:44,667 --> 00:03:46,533
Are you feeling down?

60
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:48,533
Are you scared?

61
00:03:50,167 --> 00:03:50,767
No.

62
00:03:52,433 --> 00:03:53,267
It's just about a kid.

63
00:03:58,733 --> 00:04:00,300
Do you want popcorn?

64
00:04:03,767 --> 00:04:04,500
Or water?

65
00:04:28,167 --> 00:04:31,067
[Episode 9]
[False of Heart]

66
00:04:37,033 --> 00:04:40,033
[3100 days]

67
00:05:10,100 --> 00:05:10,667
What are you doing?

68
00:05:10,800 --> 00:05:11,367
What are you doing?

69
00:05:12,100 --> 00:05:12,800
Let go!

70
00:05:13,133 --> 00:05:13,933
Let go of me!

71
00:05:13,933 --> 00:05:14,600
Call the police!

72
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:16,533
Let me go!

73
00:05:18,167 --> 00:05:19,500
Let go of me!

74
00:05:19,767 --> 00:05:20,533
What's your story?

75
00:05:21,400 --> 00:05:23,067
I was the one who helped her.

76
00:05:23,333 --> 00:05:24,233
I know.

77
00:05:24,567 --> 00:05:25,833
I mean, what are you doing on the street

78
00:05:25,833 --> 00:05:26,933
dressed like this?

79
00:05:27,333 --> 00:05:28,533
The drama club of my university

80
00:05:28,533 --> 00:05:30,100
is going to perform "The Zoo Story"

81
00:05:30,100 --> 00:05:31,067
by Edward Albee.

82
00:05:31,333 --> 00:05:33,067
I'll play a homeless man in it.

83
00:05:33,100 --> 00:05:34,567
So I wanted to experience the real life

84
00:05:34,567 --> 00:05:36,033
of a homeless man personally.

85
00:05:36,100 --> 00:05:37,233
Experience it personally?

86
00:05:37,700 --> 00:05:39,333
Are you living too comfortably?

87
00:05:40,300 --> 00:05:41,233
Officer

88
00:05:41,233 --> 00:05:42,333
you don't understand.

89
00:05:42,467 --> 00:05:44,800
Experiencing it personally is very important for an actor.

90
00:05:49,767 --> 00:05:50,267
Hello!

91
00:05:50,767 --> 00:05:51,467
Yifan

92
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:52,467
where is the college student

93
00:05:52,467 --> 00:05:53,933
who did a heroic act that you told me about?

94
00:05:57,533 --> 00:05:58,767
You really are my lucky star.

95
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:00,033
Hi

96
00:06:00,033 --> 00:06:01,233
I'm a reporter from the First News team

97
00:06:01,233 --> 00:06:03,133
of Urban Channel, Nanwu TV Station.

98
00:06:03,233 --> 00:06:04,700
Can I have an interview with you?

99
00:06:05,033 --> 00:06:05,900
Sure.

100
00:06:05,967 --> 00:06:06,800
Thank you!

101
00:06:07,767 --> 00:06:08,900
Shall we go outside?

102
00:06:09,500 --> 00:06:10,700
Okay.

103
00:06:11,467 --> 00:06:12,067
I'm going out.

104
00:06:16,967 --> 00:06:17,700
Are you okay?

105
00:06:18,300 --> 00:06:19,100
I'm fine.

106
00:06:20,133 --> 00:06:21,600
By the way, how about that street guy?

107
00:06:21,733 --> 00:06:23,567
He is currently placed in a shelter in the city.

108
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:24,100
Meanwhile

109
00:06:24,167 --> 00:06:25,800
we are also trying to contact his family.

110
00:06:26,100 --> 00:06:28,133
He has some mental health issues

111
00:06:28,233 --> 00:06:30,233
because of too much pressure from life.

112
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:33,900
Shall we start now?

113
00:06:34,967 --> 00:06:36,833
Could you briefly introduce yourself?

114
00:06:36,867 --> 00:06:37,367
Sure.

115
00:06:37,900 --> 00:06:38,900
My name is Mu Chengyun.

116
00:06:38,900 --> 00:06:40,167
I am a senior college student.

117
00:06:40,333 --> 00:06:41,700
I was experiencing the life of a homeless man

118
00:06:41,700 --> 00:06:43,900
as an actor on the street today.

119
00:06:43,967 --> 00:06:44,767
But unexpectedly

120
00:06:44,767 --> 00:06:46,233
a homeless man appeared

121
00:06:46,233 --> 00:06:47,567
standing there completely naked.

122
00:06:47,700 --> 00:06:49,067
And there was that girl.

123
00:06:49,900 --> 00:06:51,167
She was standing there too.

124
00:06:51,167 --> 00:06:52,667
I was afraid something dangerous might happen.

125
00:06:53,133 --> 00:06:54,300
You did a heroic act.

126
00:06:54,533 --> 00:06:55,533
So what did you think

127
00:06:55,533 --> 00:06:56,800
after doing it?

128
00:07:20,333 --> 00:07:21,667
Is there something on my face?

129
00:07:23,467 --> 00:07:24,067
No.

130
00:07:24,500 --> 00:07:25,767
But you were staring at me.

131
00:07:29,233 --> 00:07:30,933
I thought you looked a bit familiar.

132
00:07:36,867 --> 00:07:37,533
The notebook and pen.

133
00:07:46,067 --> 00:07:46,833
Thank you for liking me.

134
00:07:48,167 --> 00:07:49,333
I haven't acted for a long time.

135
00:07:49,333 --> 00:07:50,500
I didn't expect anyone to remember me.

136
00:07:51,733 --> 00:07:52,733
Thank you for your autograph.

137
00:07:53,333 --> 00:07:54,300
I'm leaving now.

138
00:08:11,900 --> 00:08:12,967
Thanks for your hard work, Yifan.

139
00:08:13,500 --> 00:08:14,233
It's nothing.

140
00:08:14,333 --> 00:08:15,333
You've worked hard, Tian.

141
00:08:15,333 --> 00:08:15,967
It's okay.

142
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:17,033
Tian

143
00:08:17,233 --> 00:08:18,067
Yifan

144
00:08:18,067 --> 00:08:19,500
I'll put the equipment in the car first.

145
00:08:19,700 --> 00:08:20,367
Be careful.

146
00:08:21,833 --> 00:08:22,733
By the way, Yifan

147
00:08:22,833 --> 00:08:24,367
do you still want someone to share a rental?

148
00:08:24,367 --> 00:08:25,233
I heard you mention before

149
00:08:25,233 --> 00:08:26,233
that your current roommate

150
00:08:26,233 --> 00:08:27,167
would only rent it for three months.

151
00:08:28,300 --> 00:08:29,467
How long until it expires?

152
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:30,600
I have a friend

153
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:31,933
who is looking for someone to share a rental house.

154
00:08:31,933 --> 00:08:33,167
She's a really nice girl.

155
00:08:33,300 --> 00:08:34,600
I think you two could rent a house together.

156
00:08:35,667 --> 00:08:36,567
Does she need it urgently?

157
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:37,233
No.

158
00:08:37,333 --> 00:08:38,567
She is currently living at her parents' house.

159
00:08:38,733 --> 00:08:40,167
She can wait until your roommate moves out.

160
00:08:40,467 --> 00:08:41,767
Just give her a definite answer.

161
00:08:43,500 --> 00:08:44,333
I'll ask him when I'm home.

162
00:08:44,333 --> 00:08:44,967
Okay.

163
00:08:46,433 --> 00:08:47,500
I need to answer a call, Tian.

164
00:08:47,500 --> 00:08:48,667
All right, I'll head out first then.

165
00:08:48,700 --> 00:08:49,200
Okay.

166
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:50,733
Hello?

167
00:08:51,233 --> 00:08:51,967
Where are you?

168
00:08:52,233 --> 00:08:53,467
Around the neighborhood.

169
00:08:53,567 --> 00:08:54,233
What's up?

170
00:08:54,233 --> 00:08:55,967
Come to the supermarket outside the neighborhood

171
00:08:56,300 --> 00:08:57,000
to buy some things.

172
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:57,667
Hurry.

173
00:08:57,833 --> 00:08:58,467
I can't carry them all.

174
00:09:35,233 --> 00:09:36,533
I'm at the gate of the supermarket now.

175
00:09:46,367 --> 00:09:48,667
[Mu Chengyun]

176
00:09:49,500 --> 00:09:50,700
Mu Chengyun...

177
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:53,067
Why is this name so familiar?

178
00:10:03,867 --> 00:10:07,400
[Mu Chengyun, actor]

179
00:10:09,700 --> 00:10:10,600
You like this type?

180
00:10:14,367 --> 00:10:15,533
Didn't you say you were buying something?

181
00:10:15,667 --> 00:10:16,333
Let's go.

182
00:10:16,467 --> 00:10:17,133
You haven't bought them yet?

183
00:10:17,567 --> 00:10:18,833
We are about to.

184
00:10:20,233 --> 00:10:21,833
So it's not that you can't carry them now

185
00:10:21,833 --> 00:10:22,733
but won't be able to carry them later.

186
00:10:22,733 --> 00:10:23,433
That's right.

187
00:10:35,167 --> 00:10:35,833
What's wrong?

188
00:10:36,300 --> 00:10:37,167
Why are you using another cart?

189
00:10:37,533 --> 00:10:38,467
I have things to buy too.

190
00:10:42,433 --> 00:10:43,233
Don't worry.

191
00:10:43,767 --> 00:10:44,833
I'll still help you carry your things

192
00:10:44,833 --> 00:10:46,167
if you can't carry them later.

193
00:10:51,933 --> 00:10:54,100
How's the home improvement of your house going?

194
00:10:55,667 --> 00:10:56,300
Why?

195
00:10:57,100 --> 00:10:58,967
I want to talk about it with you.

196
00:10:59,967 --> 00:11:00,900
About what?

197
00:11:02,133 --> 00:11:03,233
When are you moving out?

198
00:11:06,367 --> 00:11:07,067
Do you want to kick me out?

199
00:11:10,733 --> 00:11:11,733
Let's talk about it when the time comes.

200
00:11:12,567 --> 00:11:13,667
I'm not rushing you.

201
00:11:13,900 --> 00:11:16,300
My colleague introduced a girl to me.

202
00:11:16,567 --> 00:11:17,533
She doesn't need it urgently though.

203
00:11:18,100 --> 00:11:19,700
But we need to confirm the timing first.

204
00:11:22,833 --> 00:11:23,367
Okay.

205
00:11:23,367 --> 00:11:25,233
I'll check on the home improvement progress

206
00:11:25,367 --> 00:11:26,167
and let you know then.

207
00:11:41,167 --> 00:11:41,667
Excuse me.

208
00:11:42,100 --> 00:11:43,000
Do you need a cart?

209
00:11:43,267 --> 00:11:43,767
Yes.

210
00:11:43,800 --> 00:11:44,867
I don't need it anymore. You can take it.

211
00:11:44,867 --> 00:11:45,667
- Okay. - Thank you.

212
00:11:45,867 --> 00:11:46,367
Thank you.

213
00:11:59,000 --> 00:11:59,733
What are you doing?

214
00:12:01,233 --> 00:12:02,467
I'm calculating the price.

215
00:12:03,533 --> 00:12:04,233
Where's your cart?

216
00:12:04,767 --> 00:12:05,467
What price?

217
00:12:06,467 --> 00:12:07,567
The price of the toilet paper.

218
00:12:09,767 --> 00:12:11,300
They're all four-ply.

219
00:12:14,300 --> 00:12:15,667
Twenty-three yuan...

220
00:12:15,833 --> 00:12:17,467
One hundred and twenty grams times twelve...

221
00:12:19,333 --> 00:12:20,467
Twenty yuan...

222
00:12:20,467 --> 00:12:22,700
One hundred and forty grams times fifteen...

223
00:12:23,767 --> 00:12:24,833
Two yuan per roll.

224
00:12:25,733 --> 00:12:27,233
Twenty-three divided by ten...

225
00:12:27,933 --> 00:12:28,833
Twenty-three divided by...

226
00:12:28,833 --> 00:12:29,833
One point nine yuan...

227
00:12:30,233 --> 00:12:30,833
or so.

228
00:12:31,833 --> 00:12:32,700
Then I'll take this.

229
00:12:32,767 --> 00:12:34,300
Sure. It's cheaper.

230
00:12:37,067 --> 00:12:38,733
But it only weighs one hundred and twenty grams.

231
00:12:38,933 --> 00:12:39,933
Then take the one with ten rolls.

232
00:12:42,733 --> 00:12:43,700
I'll calculate again.

233
00:12:45,300 --> 00:12:45,967
Wen Yifan

234
00:12:46,467 --> 00:12:48,167
did you come to the supermarket for a college entrance exam?

235
00:12:48,667 --> 00:12:49,900
The calculation could take you half a year

236
00:12:49,900 --> 00:12:51,233
with your poor math skills.

237
00:12:53,700 --> 00:12:54,667
It's getting late.

238
00:12:54,667 --> 00:12:55,767
I'm afraid you'll turn in a blank paper.

239
00:12:55,767 --> 00:12:56,967
I haven't finished the calculation yet.

240
00:12:57,300 --> 00:12:58,733
I'll do the test for you this time, all right?

241
00:12:59,700 --> 00:13:00,367
The one with ten rolls.

242
00:13:00,733 --> 00:13:01,733
The one with ten rolls is a better deal.

243
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:07,567
The price has gone up?

244
00:13:08,233 --> 00:13:09,367
It seems a bit expensive.

245
00:13:22,567 --> 00:13:23,933
Hi, do you want cherries?

246
00:13:23,933 --> 00:13:24,833
They just arrived today.

247
00:13:24,933 --> 00:13:25,733
Very fresh.

248
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:26,833
You can have a taste.

249
00:13:27,100 --> 00:13:28,533
Why not take some home for your wife?

250
00:13:39,300 --> 00:13:39,967
Help me taste it.

251
00:13:44,833 --> 00:13:46,133
Your wife is so beautiful.

252
00:13:48,067 --> 00:13:49,567
Sorry, but we're not.

253
00:13:50,700 --> 00:13:52,067
Mine...

254
00:13:53,467 --> 00:13:54,167
Sang Yan's...

255
00:13:58,600 --> 00:13:59,467
Shared...

256
00:14:04,667 --> 00:14:05,367
All right.

257
00:14:05,833 --> 00:14:07,467
Do you need to pay separately?

258
00:14:07,933 --> 00:14:09,233
Together, thank you.

259
00:14:09,900 --> 00:14:10,967
I've already separated them.

260
00:14:11,233 --> 00:14:11,833
If together...

261
00:14:11,833 --> 00:14:12,533
Give me three bags, please.

262
00:14:12,767 --> 00:14:13,333
Okay.

263
00:14:15,900 --> 00:14:17,600
It won't be easy for the calculation.

264
00:14:18,367 --> 00:14:19,300
I've already separated everything.

265
00:14:19,300 --> 00:14:20,433
Mine, yours, and ours.

266
00:14:27,767 --> 00:14:28,967
We'll calculate it when we are back.

267
00:14:40,100 --> 00:14:41,167
Let me help you carry some.

268
00:14:41,967 --> 00:14:42,700
You hold the umbrella.

269
00:14:46,100 --> 00:14:46,733
Where's the umbrella?

270
00:14:47,233 --> 00:14:49,067
I may have left it in the shopping cart.

271
00:14:49,433 --> 00:14:50,000
Wait for me.

272
00:15:28,833 --> 00:15:29,533
Did you forget your umbrella?

273
00:15:30,233 --> 00:15:31,167
Shall I walk you home?

274
00:15:42,700 --> 00:15:43,533
We have an umbrella.

275
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:44,367
You can move aside.

276
00:15:45,900 --> 00:15:47,533
Are you being jealous of me?

277
00:15:47,767 --> 00:15:48,467
You?

278
00:15:49,133 --> 00:15:49,833
No.

279
00:15:51,167 --> 00:15:51,767
Hold this.

280
00:16:04,500 --> 00:16:05,700
Shift the umbrella to you a bit.

281
00:16:06,233 --> 00:16:07,067
It's blocking my view.

282
00:16:10,233 --> 00:16:10,933
Shift it more.

283
00:16:12,567 --> 00:16:14,067
Don't you know about your height?

284
00:16:16,700 --> 00:16:18,000
Then why don't you hold the umbrella?

285
00:16:18,600 --> 00:16:19,467
What are you talking about?

286
00:16:19,467 --> 00:16:20,367
You won't do a little bit of work?

287
00:16:30,700 --> 00:16:32,167
Who was that boy?

288
00:16:32,600 --> 00:16:33,467
I don't know.

289
00:16:33,667 --> 00:16:35,000
He just appeared behind me from nowhere

290
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:36,067
and asked to walk me home.

291
00:16:36,967 --> 00:16:38,600
He looks a bit familiar to me.

292
00:16:38,833 --> 00:16:40,367
There are a lot of bad people pretending to be friendly.

293
00:16:40,733 --> 00:16:41,467
Don't be silly.

294
00:16:46,233 --> 00:16:46,767
Get in the car.

295
00:17:17,733 --> 00:17:19,567
Do you want to take a hot shower?

296
00:17:19,933 --> 00:17:20,967
You'll catch a cold this way.

297
00:17:26,667 --> 00:17:28,633
His clothes are already wet

298
00:17:28,800 --> 00:17:30,067
but he's still trying to act tough.

299
00:17:38,300 --> 00:17:39,633
Cold medicine. It's hot. Be careful.

300
00:17:43,967 --> 00:17:44,933
This bag of things is all yours.

301
00:17:48,533 --> 00:17:49,233
These...

302
00:17:50,567 --> 00:17:51,167
We'll use them together.

303
00:17:52,133 --> 00:17:53,433
But it's hard to calculate.

304
00:17:53,567 --> 00:17:54,433
It's on me.

305
00:19:06,367 --> 00:19:10,867
[Mu Chengyun, actor, known for "Waking Up to Ghosts"]

306
00:19:16,967 --> 00:19:17,667
What are you doing?

307
00:19:18,100 --> 00:19:20,233
Recommend a horror movie to me

308
00:19:20,667 --> 00:19:21,367
to help me sleep.

309
00:19:29,767 --> 00:19:30,500
[Mu Chengyun, actor]

310
00:19:30,500 --> 00:19:32,867
[known for "Waking Up to Ghosts"]
A rising star for horror movies...

311
00:20:36,967 --> 00:20:38,333
Do you have to save power like this?

312
00:20:38,967 --> 00:20:40,333
Isn't it better

313
00:20:41,067 --> 00:20:42,300
to watch a horror movie like this?

314
00:20:45,333 --> 00:20:45,867
Indeed.

315
00:20:47,233 --> 00:20:49,733
It seems that people who are scared prefer to turn off the lights

316
00:20:49,733 --> 00:20:50,867
to create an atmosphere.

317
00:20:51,933 --> 00:20:52,667
They're just acting tough.

318
00:20:54,767 --> 00:20:57,533
I usually turn off the lights when I watch horror movies.

319
00:21:10,567 --> 00:21:11,133
Dad!

320
00:21:13,233 --> 00:21:14,933
I miss you so much!

321
00:21:18,100 --> 00:21:20,700
Do I look like your dad?

322
00:21:28,100 --> 00:21:29,000
I've calculated the payment.

323
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:29,900
I'll transfer it to you now.

324
00:21:37,133 --> 00:21:38,567
[Wen Yifan ¥668.00]

325
00:21:50,100 --> 00:21:50,867
Why are you laughing?

326
00:21:51,067 --> 00:21:51,867
Is it funny?

327
00:21:51,900 --> 00:21:53,633
I laugh because of the movie.

328
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:55,167
This movie is probably

329
00:21:55,167 --> 00:21:56,633
a low-budget film.

330
00:21:56,633 --> 00:21:58,700
The thing covering the actors' faces looks like flour.

331
00:22:06,333 --> 00:22:07,333
Didn't you notice

332
00:22:07,333 --> 00:22:08,767
the flour on their faces fell off

333
00:22:08,767 --> 00:22:09,667
in a fight scene?

334
00:22:11,967 --> 00:22:13,967
I don't think the movie will scare anyone.

335
00:22:20,367 --> 00:22:21,733
Haven't you seen this movie?

336
00:22:23,167 --> 00:22:23,867
Have you?

337
00:22:26,767 --> 00:22:28,333
We watched it together in Beiyu.

338
00:22:29,933 --> 00:22:31,133
Do you not remember?

339
00:22:32,167 --> 00:22:34,100
I do remember watching a movie with you.

340
00:22:34,100 --> 00:22:34,933
But...

341
00:22:35,100 --> 00:22:37,867
I just can't remember what we watched.

342
00:22:37,867 --> 00:22:38,800
Then why are you watching it?

343
00:23:07,567 --> 00:23:08,233
Hey

344
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:10,233
why did you pause it?

345
00:23:10,233 --> 00:23:11,700
Finally, here's the atmosphere

346
00:23:11,800 --> 00:23:12,800
but you are ruining it.

347
00:23:13,133 --> 00:23:14,467
Now you want the atmosphere.

348
00:23:17,367 --> 00:23:18,333
It's really him!

349
00:23:18,367 --> 00:23:19,433
[Mu Chengyun, actor]

350
00:23:25,567 --> 00:23:27,233
You can recognize him

351
00:23:27,233 --> 00:23:28,233
even if he's painted up like this.

352
00:23:33,133 --> 00:23:33,967
Where are you going?

353
00:23:34,233 --> 00:23:35,700
I'm going back to my room. I'll stop bothering you.

354
00:23:35,700 --> 00:23:37,233
It's just a horror movie.

355
00:23:37,233 --> 00:23:37,967
Do you have to be like this?

356
00:23:43,500 --> 00:23:44,533
Are you scared?

357
00:23:58,633 --> 00:23:59,533
All right, Wen Yifan.

358
00:24:13,633 --> 00:24:14,433
What do you mean?

359
00:24:15,533 --> 00:24:16,300
Just sit down.

360
00:24:17,533 --> 00:24:18,433
I know

361
00:24:18,800 --> 00:24:19,567
you're scared too.

362
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:21,333
Why did he say "too"?

363
00:24:21,633 --> 00:24:22,933
It was he who wanted to watch it.

364
00:24:22,933 --> 00:24:23,800
I'm not scared.

365
00:24:48,967 --> 00:24:50,233
So at that time

366
00:24:50,667 --> 00:24:53,867
Sang Yan fell asleep because he was scared of ghosts.

367
00:25:05,467 --> 00:25:06,700
I'm afraid...

368
00:25:07,467 --> 00:25:08,567
I might get scared later.

369
00:25:17,367 --> 00:25:17,967
It's fine.

370
00:25:19,167 --> 00:25:19,800
I'm here.

371
00:25:25,167 --> 00:25:25,867
Why are you laughing?

372
00:25:33,467 --> 00:25:34,767
You've laughed several times already.

373
00:25:37,067 --> 00:25:38,167
It's not that funny, is it?

374
00:26:00,300 --> 00:26:00,900
Good morning.

375
00:26:01,533 --> 00:26:02,300
You are up early.

376
00:26:02,700 --> 00:26:03,433
You didn't sleep well?

377
00:26:04,500 --> 00:26:05,367
It was okay.

378
00:26:05,667 --> 00:26:07,533
Where are you going

379
00:26:07,533 --> 00:26:08,467
dressed so formally in the early morning?

380
00:26:09,733 --> 00:26:11,467
I have a job interview.

381
00:26:13,467 --> 00:26:14,467
You are looking for a job?

382
00:26:15,133 --> 00:26:16,500
The jobs are looking for me.

383
00:26:16,667 --> 00:26:18,300
Many companies want me so badly.

384
00:26:18,533 --> 00:26:19,667
I picked one that I like

385
00:26:19,667 --> 00:26:20,300
and will see it today.

386
00:26:21,133 --> 00:26:22,000
How about Overtime?

387
00:26:22,633 --> 00:26:23,233
It's my bywork.

388
00:26:26,967 --> 00:26:27,633
Good luck.

389
00:26:28,633 --> 00:26:29,233
Are you going out?

390
00:26:30,233 --> 00:26:30,900
I have an appointment.

391
00:26:36,733 --> 00:26:37,900
You scored first in the written exam.

392
00:26:38,367 --> 00:26:38,967
Yes.

393
00:26:39,467 --> 00:26:40,333
Do you play games?

394
00:26:41,500 --> 00:26:42,100
Yes.

395
00:26:43,000 --> 00:26:44,900
Can you tell me more about it?

396
00:26:45,300 --> 00:26:46,767
Usually, I play

397
00:26:46,933 --> 00:26:48,000
MMO games.

398
00:26:48,000 --> 00:26:49,100
All kinds of them

399
00:26:49,100 --> 00:26:52,167
such as SLG, ACT and RPG.

400
00:26:52,867 --> 00:26:55,000
But I play turn-based games most.

401
00:26:55,067 --> 00:26:56,067
Then could you tell me

402
00:26:56,067 --> 00:26:58,767
which algorithm is the best

403
00:26:59,167 --> 00:27:00,800
when designing combat values for turn-based games?

404
00:27:01,100 --> 00:27:02,233
Probably a subtraction formula.

405
00:27:02,767 --> 00:27:04,700
Turn-based combat may look simple

406
00:27:04,700 --> 00:27:05,233
but

407
00:27:05,567 --> 00:27:06,533
every move

408
00:27:06,533 --> 00:27:08,100
is a battle of wits between players.

409
00:27:08,233 --> 00:27:10,000
The subtraction formula is simple and easy to understand.

410
00:27:10,000 --> 00:27:12,000
It reflects changes in values clearly

411
00:27:12,233 --> 00:27:14,233
and demonstrates strategic value.

412
00:27:14,867 --> 00:27:16,867
This is something the division formula lacks.

413
00:27:17,933 --> 00:27:20,233
So, what expectations do you have for our company?

414
00:27:21,000 --> 00:27:21,667
I have none.

415
00:27:22,467 --> 00:27:23,233
What about the salary?

416
00:27:23,333 --> 00:27:24,167
It's written on it.

417
00:27:25,867 --> 00:27:27,233
I'll ask you directly.

418
00:27:27,967 --> 00:27:29,733
Why did you apply

419
00:27:29,733 --> 00:27:30,667
to work in our company?

420
00:27:31,767 --> 00:27:33,367
You need to work hard

421
00:27:33,633 --> 00:27:35,133
since your look isn't an advantage.

422
00:27:35,733 --> 00:27:37,333
Don't just stay at home

423
00:27:37,333 --> 00:27:38,067
like an unemployed man every day.

424
00:27:39,300 --> 00:27:41,767
They asked you about your work today.

425
00:27:45,233 --> 00:27:46,433
To find a job.

426
00:27:47,233 --> 00:27:48,733
To find a job?

427
00:27:49,800 --> 00:27:50,333
Okay.

428
00:27:50,500 --> 00:27:51,333
The last question.

429
00:27:52,500 --> 00:27:53,633
What do you think

430
00:27:54,333 --> 00:27:55,333
is the most important thing

431
00:27:55,567 --> 00:27:56,933
to design a game?

432
00:28:00,467 --> 00:28:02,000
What would be the reason for you

433
00:28:02,667 --> 00:28:03,533
to start playing games?

434
00:28:05,933 --> 00:28:06,767
Probably loneliness.

435
00:28:08,567 --> 00:28:09,633
Everyone will feel lonely.

436
00:28:11,633 --> 00:28:13,100
They want companionship in games.

437
00:28:18,433 --> 00:28:19,500
It's okay if you want to meet.

438
00:28:19,500 --> 00:28:21,100
But why did you choose to meet around my place?

439
00:28:23,433 --> 00:28:24,433
Well, I just think

440
00:28:24,633 --> 00:28:25,733
you don't have to go too far to be here

441
00:28:26,000 --> 00:28:27,167
after you finish work.

442
00:28:27,167 --> 00:28:28,367
Then you can go home and rest

443
00:28:28,367 --> 00:28:29,467
after we finish our discussion here.

444
00:28:30,233 --> 00:28:31,367
You have got the wrong idea.

445
00:28:31,433 --> 00:28:33,133
How can I finish work that early?

446
00:28:33,133 --> 00:28:35,167
I almost work around the clock.

447
00:28:35,700 --> 00:28:36,500
Besides

448
00:28:36,500 --> 00:28:37,767
I'm not your girlfriend.

449
00:28:37,767 --> 00:28:38,933
You don't have to be so considerate.

450
00:28:41,000 --> 00:28:41,767
Maybe

451
00:28:42,167 --> 00:28:43,233
I felt this a nice place

452
00:28:43,467 --> 00:28:44,767
when I sent you home last time.

453
00:28:44,767 --> 00:28:45,567
We can hang out a bit.

454
00:28:45,800 --> 00:28:46,533
So...

455
00:28:46,700 --> 00:28:47,433
I really don't know

456
00:28:47,433 --> 00:28:49,167
what a man like you has in mind.

457
00:28:49,533 --> 00:28:50,367
What kind of man I am?

458
00:28:50,367 --> 00:28:51,767
Anyway, we are a different kind of people.

459
00:28:51,933 --> 00:28:53,167
What's the difference?

460
00:28:53,500 --> 00:28:54,533
What should I say if my grandparents ask about you

461
00:28:54,867 --> 00:28:56,500
since you don't take my orders anymore?

462
00:28:56,500 --> 00:28:57,933
It's true I'm not taking your orders anymore.

463
00:28:57,933 --> 00:28:59,733
But I can still help you as a friend.

464
00:29:05,467 --> 00:29:06,633
Thank you for calling me a friend.

465
00:29:08,067 --> 00:29:08,667
I almost forgot.

466
00:29:12,800 --> 00:29:13,533
This is for you.

467
00:29:14,967 --> 00:29:15,700
What's this?

468
00:29:16,233 --> 00:29:17,133
Look at your hands.

469
00:29:19,733 --> 00:29:21,733
They'll rot if you don't put on hand cream.

470
00:29:23,067 --> 00:29:23,700
Take it.

471
00:29:24,233 --> 00:29:24,967
Take it.

472
00:29:31,467 --> 00:29:32,567
I have a new order.

473
00:29:32,967 --> 00:29:33,900
I have to leave now.

474
00:29:33,900 --> 00:29:34,800
Don't forget to apply hand cream.

475
00:29:34,967 --> 00:29:35,733
Bye!

476
00:30:11,100 --> 00:30:11,733
Mrs. Su?

477
00:30:11,733 --> 00:30:12,967
What are you doing here?

478
00:30:13,467 --> 00:30:14,100
Hi.

479
00:30:16,667 --> 00:30:18,100
It was you who placed the order?

480
00:30:18,800 --> 00:30:20,167
Just tell me directly

481
00:30:20,167 --> 00:30:21,300
if there's anything you need help with.

482
00:30:21,300 --> 00:30:22,167
No need to place an order.

483
00:30:22,467 --> 00:30:24,167
But you're doing business.

484
00:30:24,300 --> 00:30:25,800
You don't have to be polite to me.

485
00:30:27,533 --> 00:30:28,433
But

486
00:30:28,433 --> 00:30:30,133
all you added for the order

487
00:30:30,133 --> 00:30:31,233
was "Support".

488
00:30:32,067 --> 00:30:33,233
What should I do?

489
00:30:40,333 --> 00:30:41,167
Where are we going?

490
00:30:41,633 --> 00:30:42,567
Step back a little.

491
00:30:42,567 --> 00:30:44,100
So, what kind of order is it today?

492
00:30:44,100 --> 00:30:44,900
"Caught in the act" order.

493
00:30:45,900 --> 00:30:46,867
Target:

494
00:30:47,133 --> 00:30:48,367
Su Haoan's grandfather.

495
00:30:49,533 --> 00:30:50,433
What does it mean?

496
00:30:50,767 --> 00:30:52,233
There's no time to explain it to you.

497
00:30:52,900 --> 00:30:54,933
Just do what I tell you later.

498
00:30:55,800 --> 00:30:56,500
Let's go.

499
00:30:57,333 --> 00:30:58,300
Madam

500
00:30:58,733 --> 00:31:00,233
May I ask who the leader is?

501
00:31:00,667 --> 00:31:01,500
Fang!

502
00:31:01,500 --> 00:31:02,500
Someone wants to see you.

503
00:31:02,767 --> 00:31:03,367
Okay.

504
00:31:03,367 --> 00:31:04,100
Fang.

505
00:31:04,500 --> 00:31:05,533
What's up?

506
00:31:05,533 --> 00:31:06,100
Well

507
00:31:06,100 --> 00:31:07,967
can we sign up to join you?

508
00:31:08,500 --> 00:31:09,367
You?

509
00:31:09,900 --> 00:31:10,500
Don't you see

510
00:31:10,500 --> 00:31:12,500
we are all old people?

511
00:31:12,633 --> 00:31:14,500
This is a government welfare arrangement.

512
00:31:14,500 --> 00:31:17,000
What are you young girls doing here with us?

513
00:31:17,567 --> 00:31:18,167
Fang!

514
00:31:19,433 --> 00:31:20,867
- We've been waiting for you. - Okay, just a moment.

515
00:31:20,967 --> 00:31:21,933
- Here I am. - Let's go.

516
00:31:21,967 --> 00:31:22,733
Mr. Su!

517
00:31:23,100 --> 00:31:24,233
Mr. Su!

518
00:31:24,767 --> 00:31:26,133
Lin, what brings you here?

519
00:31:27,233 --> 00:31:28,433
- Lin. - You two know each other?

520
00:31:29,233 --> 00:31:30,333
My granddaughter-in-law.

521
00:31:30,633 --> 00:31:31,633
Mr. Su

522
00:31:31,633 --> 00:31:33,567
we haven't married yet.

523
00:31:33,867 --> 00:31:34,967
Can we go together then?

524
00:31:34,967 --> 00:31:35,967
Let's just say we're dancing with you.

525
00:31:36,667 --> 00:31:37,233
Oh, here.

526
00:31:37,233 --> 00:31:38,333
My friend will join us too.

527
00:31:38,500 --> 00:31:39,067
I...

528
00:31:39,067 --> 00:31:39,800
Together.

529
00:31:40,533 --> 00:31:41,133
What do you think?

530
00:31:41,867 --> 00:31:42,567
It's okay.

531
00:31:42,733 --> 00:31:43,467
That's great!

532
00:31:43,467 --> 00:31:44,833
Thank you, Fang.

533
00:31:45,000 --> 00:31:46,833
You must be a good dancer, Mr. Su.

534
00:31:47,300 --> 00:31:49,067
He dances really well.

535
00:31:49,433 --> 00:31:50,700
That's awesome.

536
00:31:55,633 --> 00:31:56,367
I'm sorry, Mr. Su.

537
00:31:56,367 --> 00:31:57,000
I'm sorry.

538
00:31:57,167 --> 00:31:58,367
Does it hurt, Mr. Su?

539
00:31:58,900 --> 00:31:59,800
Lin

540
00:31:59,933 --> 00:32:01,133
your sense of dance rhythm

541
00:32:01,733 --> 00:32:03,533
needs some improvement.

542
00:32:03,900 --> 00:32:04,867
How about this?

543
00:32:05,000 --> 00:32:06,233
You practice over there first.

544
00:32:06,233 --> 00:32:07,700
We'll dance together after your practice, okay?

545
00:32:07,900 --> 00:32:08,900
I'm really sorry, Mr. Su.

546
00:32:08,900 --> 00:32:09,700
It's okay.

547
00:32:10,100 --> 00:32:11,100
Dian.

548
00:32:11,533 --> 00:32:12,133
I...

549
00:32:14,300 --> 00:32:15,167
Hello, Mr. Su.

550
00:32:15,167 --> 00:32:15,967
I'm Qiao

551
00:32:16,467 --> 00:32:17,333
Lin's friend.

552
00:32:17,733 --> 00:32:18,633
Please teach me.

553
00:32:19,467 --> 00:32:20,067
You?

554
00:32:21,767 --> 00:32:22,333
Okay.

555
00:32:22,533 --> 00:32:23,233
Come on.

556
00:32:36,933 --> 00:32:37,467
Very good.

557
00:32:38,367 --> 00:32:39,433
You learned it so quickly.

558
00:32:40,567 --> 00:32:41,300
Thank you, Fang.

559
00:32:43,533 --> 00:32:44,667
Listen to me, everyone.

560
00:32:44,900 --> 00:32:46,433
Let's take a break now.

561
00:32:46,433 --> 00:32:47,133
Drink some water.

562
00:32:47,133 --> 00:32:47,900
You've worked hard.

563
00:32:48,900 --> 00:32:49,633
Fang

564
00:32:50,233 --> 00:32:51,967
why didn't your husband come to dance with you?

565
00:32:51,967 --> 00:32:52,900
My husband?

566
00:32:53,900 --> 00:32:55,167
He passed away a long time ago.

567
00:32:59,233 --> 00:32:59,767
Young lady...

568
00:33:01,000 --> 00:33:01,767
You are

569
00:33:02,300 --> 00:33:03,733
Mr. Su's granddaughter-in-law?

570
00:33:04,467 --> 00:33:05,000
Yes.

571
00:33:05,133 --> 00:33:05,700
I heard

572
00:33:05,967 --> 00:33:07,633
that his wife left with someone else.

573
00:33:07,900 --> 00:33:08,933
That's not true.

574
00:33:10,433 --> 00:33:11,067
Mr. Su

575
00:33:11,167 --> 00:33:13,467
who usually dances with you?

576
00:33:13,933 --> 00:33:15,167
It depends.

577
00:33:15,167 --> 00:33:16,233
This one today.

578
00:33:16,433 --> 00:33:17,467
That one tomorrow.

579
00:33:18,933 --> 00:33:19,567
I see.

580
00:33:21,067 --> 00:33:22,167
Do you have a boyfriend?

581
00:33:22,800 --> 00:33:23,767
Not yet.

582
00:33:24,467 --> 00:33:25,900
Shall I ask my grandson

583
00:33:25,900 --> 00:33:26,967
to introduce someone to you?

584
00:33:27,533 --> 00:33:28,300
He has a friend

585
00:33:28,300 --> 00:33:29,933
who's still single.

586
00:33:29,933 --> 00:33:32,100
And he keeps bothering my grandson all day long.

587
00:33:32,233 --> 00:33:32,800
The two of them

588
00:33:32,800 --> 00:33:34,067
run a bar together.

589
00:33:37,533 --> 00:33:38,567
No, thanks.

590
00:33:38,667 --> 00:33:40,067
There's already someone I like.

591
00:33:40,667 --> 00:33:41,967
Someone you like?

592
00:33:42,467 --> 00:33:43,867
Then you should take the moves

593
00:33:43,933 --> 00:33:45,533
and pursue your own happiness.

594
00:33:46,800 --> 00:33:47,500
Otherwise

595
00:33:47,733 --> 00:33:49,233
you'll regret it

596
00:33:50,500 --> 00:33:51,733
when you come to my age.

597
00:33:52,533 --> 00:33:54,000
You have regrets too, Mr. Su?

598
00:33:57,167 --> 00:33:58,067
Come on.

599
00:34:00,233 --> 00:34:01,100
Thank you, Mr. Su.

600
00:34:03,033 --> 00:34:03,667
Mr. Su.

601
00:34:03,667 --> 00:34:04,567
I didn't expect you

602
00:34:04,567 --> 00:34:05,567
to learn so fast.

603
00:34:06,133 --> 00:34:06,900
Mr. Su

604
00:34:06,967 --> 00:34:07,767
you are such a good dancer.

605
00:34:07,767 --> 00:34:09,333
I have to dance with you someday.

606
00:34:12,200 --> 00:34:12,700
Look

607
00:34:13,467 --> 00:34:14,867
is she the lady in red?

608
00:34:16,133 --> 00:34:17,967
Which one do you mean with so many in red?

609
00:34:18,200 --> 00:34:18,933
Fang!

610
00:34:19,833 --> 00:34:21,300
She's putting her hands on him!

611
00:34:24,100 --> 00:34:25,733
It can't be that easy to guess.

612
00:34:27,300 --> 00:34:29,533
Can there be more than one?

613
00:34:31,333 --> 00:34:32,767
Today, I am inviting you

614
00:34:32,767 --> 00:34:33,667
to have some tea.

615
00:34:34,867 --> 00:34:35,600
Mr. Su

616
00:34:35,600 --> 00:34:36,967
can we join you?

617
00:34:37,100 --> 00:34:38,200
Of course.

618
00:34:38,467 --> 00:34:39,267
Come on!

619
00:34:45,500 --> 00:34:47,567
Sang Yan!

620
00:34:54,933 --> 00:34:57,067
Just call me if you need any help

621
00:34:57,200 --> 00:34:58,167
with the company.

622
00:34:58,267 --> 00:34:58,933
I'll get your back.

623
00:35:05,433 --> 00:35:05,967
What?

624
00:35:06,300 --> 00:35:06,967
Give me your hand.

625
00:35:08,333 --> 00:35:09,433
You are hired.

626
00:35:09,433 --> 00:35:10,933
We're colleagues from now on, bro.

627
00:35:11,367 --> 00:35:12,533
Why not move closer to the company?

628
00:35:12,533 --> 00:35:13,533
We can play games together after work.

629
00:35:14,167 --> 00:35:15,833
Who wants to play with you? You are a bad player.

630
00:35:18,867 --> 00:35:20,733
I think you're used to living with Wen Yifan

631
00:35:20,933 --> 00:35:21,867
and don't want to leave her.

632
00:35:22,667 --> 00:35:23,767
Let's have dinner together tonight

633
00:35:24,367 --> 00:35:25,167
for a celebration.

634
00:35:25,933 --> 00:35:27,600
I'll invite Zhong Siqiao to join us.

635
00:35:33,933 --> 00:35:34,567
Qiao

636
00:35:34,667 --> 00:35:35,667
let's have dinner together tonight.

637
00:35:37,267 --> 00:35:38,267
Invite Wen Yifan to join us too.

638
00:35:40,900 --> 00:35:41,900
I'll send you the address.

639
00:35:43,467 --> 00:35:44,000
Sang Yan!

640
00:35:44,000 --> 00:35:44,600
You're not going?

641
00:35:45,500 --> 00:35:46,067
Sang Yan!

642
00:35:52,400 --> 00:35:53,000
Have some tea.

643
00:35:53,000 --> 00:35:54,133
Thank you.

644
00:35:55,167 --> 00:35:56,533
Make yourselves at home. Just eat.

645
00:35:56,600 --> 00:35:57,533
It's so rich.

646
00:35:57,533 --> 00:35:58,433
- It smells so good. - Eat that.

647
00:35:58,433 --> 00:35:59,167
I really want to eat it.

648
00:35:59,167 --> 00:36:00,500
Just make yourselves at home.

649
00:36:00,600 --> 00:36:01,367
Feel free to eat.

650
00:36:05,733 --> 00:36:06,667
Let me tell you

651
00:36:07,133 --> 00:36:10,000
the pineapple buns here are especially authentic.

652
00:36:10,167 --> 00:36:12,833
They're exactly the same as the ones I had in Hong Kong.

653
00:36:13,200 --> 00:36:14,100
Look

654
00:36:14,600 --> 00:36:15,467
the crust

655
00:36:15,467 --> 00:36:16,300
is very flaky.

656
00:36:16,667 --> 00:36:17,933
With this butter

657
00:36:18,200 --> 00:36:18,900
it can be called

658
00:36:18,900 --> 00:36:20,467
the world's delicacy.

659
00:36:21,133 --> 00:36:23,100
What Mr. Su recommends must be delicious.

660
00:36:23,867 --> 00:36:24,500
Mr. Su

661
00:36:24,600 --> 00:36:26,967
eating too much butter isn't good for your health.

662
00:36:28,067 --> 00:36:28,567
How about

663
00:36:28,567 --> 00:36:30,167
I get you something else instead of this?

664
00:36:31,133 --> 00:36:31,967
Young lady

665
00:36:32,367 --> 00:36:33,700
people our age

666
00:36:33,767 --> 00:36:35,467
should eat whatever they want

667
00:36:35,767 --> 00:36:37,600
and date whoever they like.

668
00:36:37,600 --> 00:36:39,300
We want to live freely

669
00:36:39,300 --> 00:36:40,200
like you young people.

670
00:36:40,433 --> 00:36:41,067
That's what matters.

671
00:36:41,133 --> 00:36:42,000
Don't you think so?

672
00:36:42,133 --> 00:36:43,100
Exactly.

673
00:36:43,167 --> 00:36:43,933
Mr. Su

674
00:36:44,200 --> 00:36:45,467
do you think I'm right?

675
00:36:45,467 --> 00:36:46,433
This isn't good for your health.

676
00:36:46,433 --> 00:36:48,067
I'll order something else for you.

677
00:36:48,067 --> 00:36:49,700
Here, look at this delicious dish.

678
00:36:49,700 --> 00:36:50,467
You have to eat this.

679
00:36:50,500 --> 00:36:51,000
Come on.

680
00:36:51,033 --> 00:36:52,333
It's full of nutrition.

681
00:36:53,700 --> 00:36:55,000
- With a bite of the dish. - Here.

682
00:36:55,167 --> 00:36:56,667
- With a sip of tea. - Here's the char siu bao.

683
00:36:56,733 --> 00:36:57,900
This is good too.

684
00:36:57,900 --> 00:36:59,200
Thank you.

685
00:36:59,467 --> 00:37:00,167
Thank you.

686
00:37:00,167 --> 00:37:01,233
Eat this, Mr. Su.

687
00:37:01,233 --> 00:37:02,067
Come on.

688
00:37:06,267 --> 00:37:07,033
This is for you.

689
00:37:07,033 --> 00:37:08,533
- Thank you, Mr. Su. - Don't be too polite.

690
00:37:08,533 --> 00:37:09,200
- Let's eat. - Come on.

691
00:37:09,200 --> 00:37:10,833
[I'll be there soon.]
I got one for you too.

692
00:37:11,667 --> 00:37:12,767
We're going to the bathroom.

693
00:37:13,600 --> 00:37:14,767
And this...

694
00:37:14,767 --> 00:37:16,767
Shrimp dumpling.

695
00:37:16,767 --> 00:37:17,433
Yes!

696
00:37:18,367 --> 00:37:19,100
Which one?

697
00:37:19,867 --> 00:37:20,467
Over there.

698
00:37:22,733 --> 00:37:24,267
Look at that one next to your grandfather.

699
00:37:24,500 --> 00:37:26,167
She was serving dishes to your grandfather.

700
00:37:27,100 --> 00:37:27,767
Well

701
00:37:28,933 --> 00:37:29,933
Grandma is more beautiful.

702
00:37:29,933 --> 00:37:31,300
Grandpa may not really like her.

703
00:37:31,900 --> 00:37:33,333
Love isn't just about looks.

704
00:37:33,500 --> 00:37:34,533
I'm being honest.

705
00:37:34,533 --> 00:37:35,767
Grandma is indeed more beautiful than her.

706
00:37:36,000 --> 00:37:37,867
Men only care about looks.

707
00:37:45,000 --> 00:37:47,633
[Yu Da Shi]

708
00:37:51,367 --> 00:37:53,133
Thank you for today.

709
00:37:53,467 --> 00:37:55,133
You got up early for my grandpa's issue.

710
00:37:55,467 --> 00:37:56,467
You treat us to dinner

711
00:37:56,467 --> 00:37:57,567
just for this?

712
00:37:57,567 --> 00:37:58,367
In the beginning

713
00:37:58,600 --> 00:38:00,767
I wanted to celebrate for Sang Yan for getting a new job.

714
00:38:01,267 --> 00:38:02,600
But he wouldn't come.

715
00:38:05,333 --> 00:38:08,267
Sang Yan's new job is settled?

716
00:38:09,867 --> 00:38:10,600
Don't worry.

717
00:38:11,100 --> 00:38:12,133
I'll get his back

718
00:38:12,600 --> 00:38:13,700
in the company.

719
00:38:15,000 --> 00:38:16,333
He is really tough to deal with.

720
00:38:16,333 --> 00:38:17,100
He looks tough.

721
00:38:17,333 --> 00:38:18,000
Everything about him is tough.

722
00:38:18,567 --> 00:38:19,300
What's wrong with him?

723
00:38:20,933 --> 00:38:22,100
Talking bad about me

724
00:38:22,100 --> 00:38:22,867
when I'm not around?

725
00:38:23,333 --> 00:38:24,000
Bro!

726
00:38:24,267 --> 00:38:24,933
Why are you here?

727
00:38:25,300 --> 00:38:26,100
Surprising me?

728
00:38:26,367 --> 00:38:27,167
Good.

729
00:38:29,367 --> 00:38:30,200
Our hero is here.

730
00:38:30,200 --> 00:38:30,933
Come on.

731
00:38:31,333 --> 00:38:32,333
Let's have a drink.

732
00:38:32,667 --> 00:38:35,000
Toast to Sang Yan for joining my company.

733
00:38:35,167 --> 00:38:35,833
Congratulations.

734
00:38:40,433 --> 00:38:41,133
But, Sang Yan

735
00:38:41,133 --> 00:38:42,367
why did you suddenly want a job?

736
00:38:42,933 --> 00:38:44,133
After he graduated

737
00:38:44,300 --> 00:38:45,933
he went straight to a big company in Nanwu.

738
00:38:46,100 --> 00:38:47,533
But who knows what got into him?

739
00:38:47,533 --> 00:38:48,333
He suddenly quit.

740
00:38:48,667 --> 00:38:49,567
Stop talking too much.

741
00:38:49,733 --> 00:38:50,233
Drink it.

742
00:38:52,533 --> 00:38:53,100
Okay.

743
00:38:55,133 --> 00:38:55,700
Yifan

744
00:38:56,067 --> 00:38:57,067
thank you for today.

745
00:38:57,333 --> 00:38:57,967
Thank you.

746
00:38:58,600 --> 00:38:59,200
You are welcome.

747
00:38:59,700 --> 00:39:00,733
I'm having an off day anyway.

748
00:39:00,833 --> 00:39:01,833
Consider it spending time with Qiao.

749
00:39:04,133 --> 00:39:04,733
What do you think

750
00:39:05,067 --> 00:39:06,200
first love even means?

751
00:39:07,100 --> 00:39:08,667
What's the meaning of being together for decades?

752
00:39:09,067 --> 00:39:10,567
I really feel bad for my grandma.

753
00:39:10,867 --> 00:39:12,167
Grandpa was her first love.

754
00:39:13,133 --> 00:39:14,367
He's already at an old age

755
00:39:14,467 --> 00:39:15,367
but is still messing around

756
00:39:15,367 --> 00:39:16,433
with those dance teachers.

757
00:39:17,133 --> 00:39:18,133
He's really troublesome.

758
00:39:24,300 --> 00:39:25,300
I will definitely ask her

759
00:39:25,300 --> 00:39:26,167
why she would ruin another woman's family

760
00:39:26,167 --> 00:39:27,500
when I find her out!

761
00:39:27,533 --> 00:39:28,900
That's not what I meant.

762
00:39:29,600 --> 00:39:31,167
I want to ask you

763
00:39:31,533 --> 00:39:32,867
to help me find out

764
00:39:32,867 --> 00:39:33,933
if she's reliable.

765
00:39:35,133 --> 00:39:36,267
Is she reliable?

766
00:39:37,700 --> 00:39:40,467
If she is reliable

767
00:39:40,933 --> 00:39:43,467
and they truly love each other

768
00:39:43,900 --> 00:39:45,300
I will support them.

769
00:39:46,433 --> 00:39:47,133
Mrs. Su

770
00:39:47,367 --> 00:39:49,333
you are too good to her.

771
00:39:52,000 --> 00:39:53,367
Do you think

772
00:39:53,900 --> 00:39:55,667
if it's good love

773
00:39:55,733 --> 00:39:57,333
when neither of them is happy

774
00:39:58,100 --> 00:39:59,767
being together?

775
00:40:01,133 --> 00:40:03,600
Forcing it won't bring happiness.

776
00:40:03,967 --> 00:40:05,167
What if

777
00:40:05,167 --> 00:40:06,700
he happens to meet the one

778
00:40:06,933 --> 00:40:09,700
he feels is the most important in life?

779
00:40:10,067 --> 00:40:10,967
What should we do?

780
00:40:13,967 --> 00:40:14,967
Mrs. Su

781
00:40:15,100 --> 00:40:16,100
you'd better

782
00:40:16,367 --> 00:40:18,667
have a good talk with Mr. Su first.

783
00:40:18,700 --> 00:40:19,867
What should we talk about?

784
00:40:20,200 --> 00:40:22,733
Lately, he forgets everything I tell him.

785
00:40:22,967 --> 00:40:25,333
He doesn't even remember my birthday.

786
00:40:25,567 --> 00:40:27,567
His mind is no longer on me.

787
00:40:27,967 --> 00:40:29,933
Why should I hold on to him?

788
00:40:36,833 --> 00:40:38,467
It seems that, for men

789
00:40:38,467 --> 00:40:39,533
first love is nothing to them.

790
00:40:41,333 --> 00:40:43,867
Maybe only girls care more about their first love.

791
00:40:46,733 --> 00:40:47,533
Not necessarily.

792
00:40:48,100 --> 00:40:49,567
The place of first love

793
00:40:49,900 --> 00:40:51,333
is irreplaceable.

794
00:40:54,600 --> 00:40:56,067
You're talking as if you really understand.

795
00:40:58,933 --> 00:40:59,867
Talk less.

796
00:41:00,767 --> 00:41:01,300
Cheers!

797
00:41:05,667 --> 00:41:13,033
[Episode 9]
[False of Heart, Honest of Action]

798
00:41:28,333 --> 00:41:32,967
[The story is not over yet...]

799
00:41:59,267 --> 00:42:03,433
How many loved your moments of glad grace

800
00:42:05,333 --> 00:42:07,367
and loved your beauty with love

801
00:42:08,533 --> 00:42:10,000
false or true.

802
00:42:15,500 --> 00:42:17,900
But one man loved the pilgrim soul in you

803
00:42:19,300 --> 00:42:23,567
and loved the sorrows of your changing face.

804
00:42:31,867 --> 00:42:33,200
♪Even the strongest heart♪

805
00:42:33,367 --> 00:42:35,033
♪Can waver♪

806
00:42:35,267 --> 00:42:38,467
♪And doubt its fire♪

807
00:42:38,733 --> 00:42:40,367
♪But you never lost faith in me♪

808
00:42:40,367 --> 00:42:42,033
♪In every battle, every dream I chased♪

809
00:42:42,233 --> 00:42:44,933
♪There is meaning in every step I made♪

810
00:42:45,767 --> 00:42:51,733
♪Through the storm, through the endless night♪

811
00:42:52,067 --> 00:42:53,733
♪You were there, shining like a light♪

812
00:42:53,733 --> 00:42:55,400
♪Warm and bright♪

813
00:42:55,567 --> 00:42:59,267
♪Standing right by my side♪

814
00:42:59,733 --> 00:43:05,833
♪It was you, striding toward me through the storm♪

815
00:43:06,200 --> 00:43:13,133
♪It was you, always cheering me on♪

816
00:43:13,267 --> 00:43:16,267
♪The road is rough♪

817
00:43:16,600 --> 00:43:20,733
♪The rain won't stop♪

818
00:43:20,933 --> 00:43:24,867
♪But with you here♪

819
00:43:25,167 --> 00:43:31,200
♪I fear no dark♪

820
00:43:34,433 --> 00:43:38,033
♪Every thought, every memory is filled with you♪

821
00:43:38,367 --> 00:43:41,833
♪Marking our youth with every step we took♪

822
00:43:42,133 --> 00:43:44,000
♪When the downpour falls from the sky♪

823
00:43:44,000 --> 00:43:47,633
♪You're the one holding out an umbrella for me♪

824
00:43:48,000 --> 00:43:51,567
♪When the white dove brings the news♪

825
00:43:51,933 --> 00:43:55,367
♪You're the first I want to tell♪

826
00:43:55,767 --> 00:44:04,400
♪I won't give up. I'll stay right here with you♪

827
00:44:09,000 --> 00:44:15,200
♪It was you, striding toward me through the storm♪

828
00:44:16,033 --> 00:44:22,467
♪It was you, always cheering me on♪

829
00:44:22,467 --> 00:44:25,633
♪The road is rough♪

830
00:44:26,133 --> 00:44:30,067
♪The rain won't stop♪

831
00:44:30,267 --> 00:44:32,933
♪But with you here♪

832
00:44:33,133 --> 00:44:36,967
♪I will never give up♪

833
00:44:37,233 --> 00:44:43,333
♪You are my courage, my hope for the sky beyond♪

834
00:44:43,833 --> 00:44:49,667
♪You are my light, shining through every night♪

835
00:44:50,233 --> 00:44:53,067
♪Even if I have to walk alone someday♪

836
00:44:53,533 --> 00:44:56,367
♪I'll never truly be on my own♪

837
00:44:57,400 --> 00:45:01,933
♪'Cause knowing you're here♪

838
00:45:02,367 --> 00:45:08,967
♪I can brave the dark ahead♪

839
00:45:10,767 --> 00:45:12,033
[Huge thanks to everyone involved and to all the fans of The First Frost!]

840
00:45:12,033 --> 00:45:13,167
[Treat yourself well, and the world will hold more love for you!]
